{{primitive|g f/y<br>g f\y}}

'''while''' and '''scan-while''' are adverbs that apply a [[monadic]] function to a given noun <code>y</code> as long as the condition in <code>g</code> returns a [[truthy]] value when applied to <code>y</code>.

while(<code>/</code>) produces a single value, the final value.

Scan-while(<code>\</code>) produces a list of all intermediate values.

<pre>
 {6>#x}{x,2*x}/2 3
2 3 4 6 4 6 8 12

 {6>#x}{x,2*x}\2 3
(2 3
 2 3 4 6
 2 3 4 6 4 6 8 12)
</pre>

